\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 6. G. fibrosa} (Desf.) Schultes & Schultes fil., {\i op. cit.} 552 (1829) (incl.{\i  G. rigida }Boiss. & Spruner). Plants solitary. Stem 2-8 cm. Bulb usually covered with recurved fibrous roots and with a collar up to 0·8 cm. Basal leaf flat. Perianth segments 14-20 mm. {\i Dry, clayey slopes. Aegean region.} Gr. ({\i S.W. Asia}.)
