\pard\f0\fs28   Perhaps conspecific with {\b 5}; plants intermediate between {\b 5} & {\b 6} occur, and some of the variation may be due to ecological factors. Further study is required. Plants like {\b 6} but with the bulb bearing stolons terminating in bulbils have been called {\b G. commutata} C. Koch, {\i Linnaea }{\b 22}: 227 (1849). They occur in Kriti and may represent a distinct species.
